{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:05:53.117692+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_5c7fe31e-c8a6-4313-be08-bbd48a4a86ef"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_6ec34348-94c5-4050-9f95-3b6dae872719"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "e6ba1f36-0586-4aa2-bf47-f995af01e8e5", "tool_call_id": "call_00_GtYiKSfg9VrffWcL4j6H1532", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:05:59.609290+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer\n\nThe package installs the command-line tool **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion). Based on the source code in `src/gwc/cli.py` and the README, here is what `gwc` currently does:\n\n### Installed command\n\n**`gwc`** — registered via the entry point `gwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"` in `pyproject.toml`.\n\n### What it does\n\n`gwc` provides three subcommands that wrap common git workflows for solo developers:\n\n1. **`gwc status-summary`**  \n   Prints a one-line summary of the current branch, including:\n   - Current branch name\n   - Ahead/behind count vs. its tracked upstream (if any)\n   - Number of staged / unstaged / untracked files\n\n2. **`gwc branch-name <issue-number> <short-slug>`**  \n   Generates a conventional branch name for an issue (e.g., `issue-42-add-login`). It only prints the name; it does **not** create the branch. You can pipe it into `git checkout -b`.\n\n3. **`gwc clean-merged`**  \n   Lists local branches that are fully merged into `main` and offers to delete them. By default it runs in dry-run mode (prints what *would* be deleted). Pass `--apply` to actually delete them.\n\nThe tool intentionally avoids network operations (push, pull, fetch, clone) and history rewriting — those are left to plain `git`. It also reads an optional `.gwcrc` TOML config file from the repository root for settings like branch-name prefix and protected branches.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 523, "prompt_tokens": 5896, "total_tokens": 6419, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 168, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5248}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 5248, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 648}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "cf9d3438-9be1-4272-96a3-37d2776daf63", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea41e-f65e-74e3-a308-2121f1fa9f6e-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5896, "output_tokens": 523, "total_tokens": 6419, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5248}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 168}}}}]}}}
